  "texts": [
    "Now consider the following back conditions:B1 R ′ i (h(x)) ⊆ h[R i (x)]; B2 cl(⇓R ′ i (h(x))) ⊆ cl(⇓h[R i (x)]); B3 int(cl(⇓R ′ i (h(x)))) ⊆ int(cl(⇓h[R i (x)])).B1-B3 clarify the earlier back conditions for R i as follows.Fact 3.3 (Back Conditions for R i).",
    "For any possibility frames F and F ′ and function h: F → F ′:1.",
    "B1 implies B2, which implies B3;2. p-R-back is equivalent to B1; 3.",
    "R-back is equivalent to ⇓R ′ i (h(x)) ⊆ cl(⇓h[R i (x)]), which is equivalent to B2; 4.",
    "B3 implies the right-to-left direction of R-matching; 5. if F ′ is a full possibility frame, then B3 is equivalent to the right-to-left direction of R-matching.Proof."
